<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
See Also
Bluetongue, sheep - Europe: RFI 20001124.2041
Date: 26 Nov 2000
From: Chris Griot <christian.griot@ivi.admin.ch>
Source: OIE Disease Page
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_53.HTM#Sec0>
Bluetongue in Spain:
In the Balearic Islands
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: 1960).
Emergency report
Translation of the summary of 2 faxes received on 6 and 13 Oct 2000 from Dr
Quintiliano Perez Bonilla, Director General of Animal Production, Ministry
of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
Final date of the report: 11 Oct 2000.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 9 Oct 2000.
Estimated date of first infection: 29 Sep 2000.
Outbreaks:
Location: Capdepera (island of Majorca)
No. of outbreaks: 1
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species: ovi
susceptible: 1315
cases: 127
deaths: 28
destroyed: 99
slaughtered: 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Animal Health Investigation Centre
(Valdeolmos).
B. Diagnostic tests used: PCR (polymerase chain reaction).
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: under study.
B. Mode of spread: biological vectors (_Culicoides_ spp.).
C. Other epidemiological details: disease limited to the Balearic Islands.
This insular territory
is isolated from the rest of Spain.
Control measures during reporting period: control of arthropods; modified
stamping out; quarantine and movement control inside the country;
vaccination prohibited.
